# Copy to ~/.hermes/.env — curated subset relevant to this repo's setup.
# Never commit the filled-in .env — this file is placeholders only.
# Full reference: config/dot_env.dist (genuine installer template, kept
# unmodified — check there before assuming any key not shown here).

# --- Cloud fallback provider (optional) ---
# Confirmed real, but NOT configured here — the real key is `fallback_model:`
# (singular) directly in config.yaml, not an .env variable. See the
# commented-out block at the bottom of config/config.yaml for the exact
# shape and full list of supported providers.
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=

# --- Discord bot auth ---
# Confirmed real keys — but don't hand-type these. `hermes gateway setup`
# (see README.md §7) writes them into ~/.hermes/.env automatically when
# you walk through its interactive prompts. They're absent from the
# genuine dot_env.dist template because that file only pre-populates
# always-present keys, not ones a setup wizard fills in on demand.
# DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=
# DISCORD_ALLOWED_USERS=

# --- Hermes API timeout tuning (legacy env-var fallback — confirmed real
# from config.yaml's own comments, but NOT part of the actively-templated
# dot_env.dist, so treat as a secondary option, not the primary path) ---
# The primary path is config.yaml's per-provider request_timeout_seconds /
# stale_timeout_seconds (see cli-config.yaml.dist lines ~128-141).
# HERMES_API_TIMEOUT=1800
# HERMES_API_CALL_STALE_TIMEOUT=90

# --- Ollama backend notes (not read from this file — informational only) ---
# Ollama is managed via `brew services`, not an env var here. See README.md
# §5 for OLLAMA_MAX_LOADED_MODELS / OLLAMA_NUM_PARALLEL, which go in the
# brew-managed launchd plist's EnvironmentVariables block, not this file.
# Confirm `ollama --version` is 0.22.0 or later — earlier builds predate
# the llama.cpp Gemma 4 fixes, particularly around tool-calling reliability.
